rstood by examining it from social, individual and contextual dimensions, in relation to actual people. Authenticity is a problem not just for language acquisition but one which affects us as individuals belonging to society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexGlobalization. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aAuthenticity.  aChaos/complexity theory .  aComplexity theory.  aCross-cultural exchanges.  aELF.  aELT.  aGlobal English.  aIdentity.  aJapanese learners of English.  aL2 varieties of English.  aLanguage teaching.  aMotivation.  aNative speaker.  aSLA.  aTESOL.  aThe Self.  aWorld Englishes.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066311208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060670640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178309568140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781783095681423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781783095681/original  a978-3-11-060670-6  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066311-2  MultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK